text.section:
For the following counties and municipal corporations the rate of interest for each month or fraction of a month that county or municipal corporation property tax or taxing district property tax is overdue is:
1% for Garrett County;
1% for the City of Salisbury;
1% for Washington County;
1% for Somerset County; and
the rate set by law by:
the governing body of a county that has adopted a charter form of government under Article XI-A of the Maryland Constitution;
the governing body of:
Allegany County;
the City of Annapolis;
Berlin, not exceeding 1.5%;
Caroline County, not exceeding 1%;
Cecil County, or any municipal corporation in Cecil County, not exceeding 1%;
Dorchester County;
the City of Frederick, not exceeding 1%, that is set on or before the date of finality;
Frederick County, not exceeding 1%, that is set on or before the date of finality;
Ocean City, not exceeding 1.5%;
Pocomoke City, not exceeding 1.5%;
the Town of Princess Anne, not exceeding 1.5%;
Kent County or any municipal corporation in Kent County;
Queen Anne's County or any municipal corporation in Queen Anne's County;
Snow Hill, not exceeding 1.5%;
Worcester County, not exceeding 1.5%;
Calvert County;
St. Mary's County;
the City of Taneytown;
the City of Cambridge; or
Mardela Springs, not exceeding 1%; or
the Mayor and City Council of Baltimore City for Baltimore City, if the rate is set on or before June 30 for the following taxable year.
